title: 1950, Michigan State Spartans
description: The program for the 1950 ND Michigan State game in which ND lost by 3 points on their home turf. It depicts two men wearing all white outfits, including white ties, jumping up and down cheering. The man in the front has both his arms extended upwards while the man in the back is pointing in the distance and holds a noise amplifier in his other hand. In the left background, a player wearing gold pants as part of the uniform is defeatedly doing pushups or standing up slowly after having fallen down. In the right side background, there is a referee pointing at the ground with one hand, upwards with the other, and aggressively blowing his whistle.

source: University of Notre Dame, University Archives
